    First paragraph. Amy normally hated Monday mornings, but this year was different! She fell in love with math
counting expressions like: [ 8 2 7 4 + * -]. End of first paragraph.
    Second paragraph. After school, Kamal took the girls to the old house. It was very old and very dirty too.
There was rubbish everywhere. The windows were broken and the walls were damp. It was scary. On the wall it was
written [-5 -2 / 9 + 8 -] Amy didn’t like it. “We’re going to take photos for the school art competition,” said Kamal.
End of second paragraph.
    Third paragraph. Next evening was Halloween. The girls were at the school disco. “Are you better now?” asked Tara.
“I’m fine,” said Amy. Tara looked around. “I don’t know, I don’t want to see Kamal again,” said Amy. “Come on, let’s
dance!” End of third paragraph.

